Collector: Angela De Palma-Dow and Ben Luukkonen
Locality: Dearborn, UM Dearborn Environmental Interpretive Center John Montieth Blvd
Habitat: Growing  in a man-made reflecting pond with concrete bottom. Other species growing in pond are mostly White water lily, duckweed, and Eleocharis spp. This is the first cofnirmed case of Yellow-Flaoting heart in MI.  Some of the staff at that location say that Clara Ford probably planted the Yellow Heart when she used the reflection pond as a water feature in her large rose garden, but some staff say that the plant has only been in the pond for 20 years or so.  There is not a consensus on how and when this invasive was introduced into this man-made pond.
